le-0-generateMetadata-2026-05-11T21-55-28-209173Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.xmlunit:xmlunit-legacy:2.10.2/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n\nThe preserved branch already contains a concrete test plus candidate metadata updates, and later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/org.xmlunit:xmlunit-legacy:2.10.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-11T22-03-06-988501Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.xmlunit:xmlunit-legacy:2.10.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-11T22-03-33-686606Z.log` passed, so this looks like a native-metadata/env follow-up rather than a pure test-authoring failure.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch changes, especially `tests/src/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-legacy/2.10.2/src/test/java/org_xmlunit/xmlunit_legacy/Jaxp13XpathEngineTest.java`, `metadata/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-legacy/2.10.2/reachability-metadata.json`, and the added `metadata/org.xmlunit/xmlunit-core/2.9.1/reachability-metadata.json` entries.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.xmlunit:xmlunit-legacy:2.10.2` in an environment with a working native-image agent and confirm the native path still passes.\n3. If validation stays green, continue from the preserved branch and open the PR with the minimal passing changes."}}
